  <discussion>The red-dotted perigynia of Carex triangularis separates the species from all other taxa in the section; however, it is similar to C. annectens in the relative lengths of leaves and flowering stems, and in the yellow-brown, ovate perigynia that are larger and broader than in C. annectens.</discussion>
